        <argsstring></argsstring>
        <name>StorageDataFolder</name>
        <qualifiedname>UTryllRuntimeSettings::StorageDataFolder</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Project-relative folder that node storage paths (string / embedded string storages, voice hotwords) resolve against for this session.</para>
<para>Stored relative to the Unreal project directory in editor builds (e.g. &quot;Content/TryllStringStorages&quot;) and relative to the packaged game directory in shipping builds. <ref refid="class_u_tryll_runtime_settings_1ad24e6fc9811c134de92dc39fd4f86597" kindref="member">ResolveStorageDataFolderForServer()</ref> converts this to an absolute path before ConfigureSession sends it on the wire.</para>
<para>Leave empty to use the server&apos;s configured storage root. Relative paths in node params resolve against the resolved folder; paths that escape it are rejected. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
